<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241478>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Specimens of Lestes nigriceps from Cambodia, Mondulkiri, 15 km NNE of Sen Monorom: a–b—males; bfemale 1; c—female 2." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241478/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241480>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Details of the male specimen shown in Fig. 3a of Lestes nigriceps from Cambodia, Mondulkiri, 15 km NNE of Sen Monorom: a—head, dorsal view; b— ditto, frontal view; c—paraprocts, dorsal view; d—S10 and appendages, dorsal view; editto, lateral view; f— ditto ventral view, g—left hind wing. Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241480/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241476>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Lestes nigriceps in nature; Cambodia, Mondulkiri Province, a grassy swamp in a large glade in an open deciduous dipterocarp forest 15 km NNE of Sen Monorom, 12.5771 N 107.2587 E, 455 m a.s.l., 27 vii 2018: a—male; b–c—tandem." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241476/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241482>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Head, synthorax and S1–2 of four male specimens of Lestes nigriceps from Cambodia, Mondulkiri, 15 km NNE of Sen Monorom; a–b—the specimen shown in Figs. 3a and 4; d—the specimen shown in Fig. 3b; a—dorsal view; b–e—lateral view. Scale bar 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241482/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241474>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Lectotype (male) of Lestes nigriceps in BMNH (NHMUK 013384634) (courtesy of Benjamin Price) (a–g) and its drawing in the original description (Fraser 1924: plate IX: 6) (h): a—general habitus (dorsal view) and labels; b—head, thorax, left wings and base of abdomen, dorsal view; c—general habitus, lateral view; c—head, thorax and base of abdomen, lateral view; general habitus, lateral view; e, h—end of abdomen, dorsal view; c—general habitus, lateral view; f—ditto, lateral view; g—paraprocts, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241474/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241484>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Female specimens 1 (a) and 2 (b–f) of Lestes nigriceps from Cambodia, Mondulkiri, 15 km NNE of Sen Monorom: a, b—head, synthorax and S1–2, lateral view; c—head, dorsal view; d—ditto, e–f—end of abdomen,lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241484/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241488>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Anal appendages of two male specimens of Lestes viridulus (India, Karnataka, Kodagu District, Makutta, 22 iii 2013, Krushnamegh Kunte leg.) from National Centre for Biological Sciences, Tata Institute of Fundamental Research, Bangalore (courtesy of Shantanu Joshi): a, c—specimen PS598; b, d—specimen PS597; a, b—dorsal view; c, d—ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241488/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3241486>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Habitat of Lestes nigriceps in Cambodia, Mondulkiri, 15 km NNE of Sen Monorom, 12.5771 N 107.2587 E, 455 m a.s.l.: a grassy swamp in a large glade in an open deciduous dipterocarp forest, 27 vii 2018." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3241486/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

